{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/common_user_token"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For security reasons, chat history by default has a temporary nature and gets killed when providing another credentials into "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/Jivo","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"code":"Jivo\/session","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/JVSessionController\/setup(widgetID:clientIdentity:)"},{"type":"text","text":", or by calling "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/Jivo","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"code":"Jivo\/session","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.cocoapods.JivoSDK\/documentation\/JivoSDK\/JVSessionController\/shutDown()"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It means, for example, if your client logs-out and then logs-in again, you may see him as entirely new client."},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"text","text":"Even in case he uses the same login credentials, and even in case you provide the same user_token for him into SDK."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To keep chat history alive between login sessions, you have to generate JWT token and use it as user_token."},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"text":"Below, we explain how to do that.","type":"text"}]},{"level":2,"anchor":"1-Prepare-secret","type":"heading","text":"#1: Prepare secret"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"First, you need to create your global ","